### ============================================================
### SportLink - Booking Service - HTTP request samples
### ============================================================
### Service runs on http://localhost:8084
### Two bookings are seeded on startup by DataInitializer:
###   - bk-001  status=PENDING    payment=PENDING (50.00 EUR)
###   - bk-002  status=CONFIRMED  payment=PAID    (75.50 EUR)
###
### Endpoints that work standalone (no other service required):
###   * GET    /api/bookings
###   * GET    /api/bookings/{id}
###   * PUT    /api/bookings/{id}/confirm
###   * POST   /api/bookings/{id}/refund
###
### Endpoints that need a peer service running:
###   * POST   /api/bookings                  -> needs Scheduling Service @ :8085
###   * PUT    /api/bookings/{id}/cancel      -> needs Scheduling Service @ :8085
###   * GET    /api/bookings/facilities/...   -> needs Search Service     @ :8086
### These return 503 Service Unavailable until peer services are up.
### ============================================================


### ---------- 1. Swagger UI (open in browser) -----------------
GET http://localhost:8084/swagger-ui/index.html


### ---------- 2. OpenAPI spec (raw JSON) ---------------------
GET http://localhost:8084/v1/api-docs


### ============================================================
### READ - GET endpoints (work without peer services)
### ============================================================

### 3. List all bookings (no filters)  -> returns the 2 seeded bookings
GET http://localhost:8084/api/bookings


### 4. Get a single booking by ID  (PENDING one)
GET http://localhost:8084/api/bookings/bk-001


### 5. Get a single booking by ID  (CONFIRMED one)
GET http://localhost:8084/api/bookings/bk-002


### 6. Get a booking that does not exist  -> 404 Not Found
GET http://localhost:8084/api/bookings/does-not-exist


### ============================================================
### FILTER - GET /api/bookings with query params
### ============================================================

### 7. Filter by activityId
GET http://localhost:8084/api/bookings?activityId=act-200


### 8. Filter by sportCenterId
GET http://localhost:8084/api/bookings?sportCenterId=sc-100


### 9. Filter by bookingStatus = PENDING
GET http://localhost:8084/api/bookings?bookingStatus=PENDING


### 10. Filter by bookingStatus = CONFIRMED
GET http://localhost:8084/api/bookings?bookingStatus=CONFIRMED


### 11. Filter by bookingStatus = CANCELLED  -> empty list initially
GET http://localhost:8084/api/bookings?bookingStatus=CANCELLED


### 12. Combined filter: sportCenterId + bookingStatus
GET http://localhost:8084/api/bookings?sportCenterId=sc-101&bookingStatus=CONFIRMED


### 13. All three filters at once
GET http://localhost:8084/api/bookings?activityId=act-200&sportCenterId=sc-100&bookingStatus=PENDING


### ============================================================
### STATE TRANSITIONS - work without peer services
### ============================================================

### 14. Confirm bk-001:  PENDING -> CONFIRMED, payment PENDING -> PAID
PUT http://localhost:8084/api/bookings/bk-001/confirm


### 15. Try to confirm an already-CONFIRMED booking  -> 409 Conflict
PUT http://localhost:8084/api/bookings/bk-002/confirm


### 16. Try to refund a CONFIRMED (not yet cancelled) booking  -> 409 Conflict
###     Refund only allowed when bookingStatus=CANCELLED + payment=PAID.
POST http://localhost:8084/api/bookings/bk-002/refund


### ============================================================
### CREATE - needs Scheduling Service @ :8085
### Returns 503 Service Unavailable when Scheduling is down.
### ============================================================

### 17. Create a new booking (full payload)
POST http://localhost:8084/api/bookings
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "sportCenterId": "sc-100",
    "activityId":    "act-500",
    "timeSlotId":    "ts-900",
    "payment": {
        "amount":        60.00,
        "currency":      "EUR",
        "paymentMethod": "CARD"
    }
}


### 18. Create another booking - different sport center / activity
POST http://localhost:8084/api/bookings
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "sportCenterId": "sc-200",
    "activityId":    "act-700",
    "timeSlotId":    "ts-901",
    "payment": {
        "amount":        100.00,
        "currency":      "EUR",
        "paymentMethod": "PAYPAL"
    }
}


### ============================================================
### CANCEL  - needs Scheduling Service @ :8085
### ============================================================

### 19. Cancel a confirmed booking - releases slot via Scheduling Service
PUT http://localhost:8084/api/bookings/bk-002/cancel


### 20. After cancel succeeds, refund becomes valid:
###     bookingStatus=CANCELLED + paymentStatus=PAID -> REFUNDED
POST http://localhost:8084/api/bookings/bk-002/refund


### 21. Try to cancel an already-cancelled booking  -> 409 Conflict
PUT http://localhost:8084/api/bookings/bk-002/cancel


### 22. Try to refund twice  -> 409 Conflict
###     (paymentStatus is REFUNDED now, not PAID)
POST http://localhost:8084/api/bookings/bk-002/refund


### ============================================================
### SEARCH  - needs Search Service @ :8086
### Delegates synchronously to GET /api/v1/search?entityType=FACILITY
### ============================================================

### 23. Search facilities by sport type
GET http://localhost:8084/api/bookings/facilities/search?sportType=BASKETBALL


### 24. Search facilities by sport + location
GET http://localhost:8084/api/bookings/facilities/search?sportType=BASKETBALL&location=Tartu


### 25. Search facilities filtered by a specific time slot
GET http://localhost:8084/api/bookings/facilities/search?sportType=FOOTBALL&location=Tallinn&timeSlotId=ts-300


### 26. Search with no filters  -> all facilities the Search Service has indexed
GET http://localhost:8084/api/bookings/facilities/search
